review.reviewBody: The Pancit Palabok (Thin Rice Noodles) is tasty but very expensive for the amount you get.
So disappointed for the portions! Given for the expensive price. Its not worth it.

We always buy the Bistek tagalog and it comes in rectangular  black  plastic container which was so worth for the price of $26 + taxes + tips. But our last order, it came in a small white paper cup which was like rip off.  

Taste was always amazing but the serving size was not so worth the price.
I love the Sizzling Tofu and Miki Bihon. I didn't really like the spring rolls. There's not much flavor in it.  Over all I would still support this place

The quality at Max's has gone down the last few years. the Lumpiang Shanghai (Egg Roll) tastes old and soggy. The Beef Kare-Kare (Beef Peanut Stew) doesnt taste like how kare kare should be. it taste like a bland watery beef curry (it's a watery orangey stew, if you are lucky, you can find a few pieces of beef meat). very disappointing. Not worth the $$$
